external_knowledge:
- "top 3 users" implies the three users with the highest access counts for each data entry; 
- "accessed the most" refers to the users with the highest access counts; 
- demographic data entry is assumed to be identifiable by the combination of data_id and year.

- "youngest age group" refers to the age group with age_group_id = 1; 
- "this year" refers to the year with is_current = 1 in the years table; 
- "researchers" refers to users belonging to the 'Research' department.

sql:
SELECT source_name AS Highest_Source_Name
FROM data_sources
WHERE source_id = (SELECT MAX(source_id) FROM data_sources);
